ering these new research items together, then deciding who will use them and for what.<br>
<br>
I am guild banker, and these new items have started coming in.  Generally with static items like weapons and spell scrolls, it is pretty clear when someone requests an item if it would best serve the guild in their hands.  These new research items, however, are a whole new deal.  They can be used in a variety of combinations, to make spells in a range of levels and for different classes.  This has started to ratchet a bit of tension in who gets what that never really surfaced before.  By way of background, my guild is generally nbg, and I am not relishing having to decide who gets gizmo X when 2 people both have legitimate interests for entirely different uses of the same item.<br>
<br>
How have various guilds handled this?  What has worked, what hasn't? Is this simply not a problem and if so, what do you do that works?<br>
<br>
I aim for being pretty even-handed and democratic about the Armory of my guild, and this is really the first time that items are so sought after, that my decisions may be misconstrued unless I gather information and form a fair policy.  This post is part of my efforts in that regard.<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for any advice!<br>
