<br>
One Member took on the duanting task of collecting all research items. Individual members were responsible for notifying her of their need for researched spells. If it was a spell the guild really needed, it got precedece. If the components were not in high demand for a needed spell she would make any spell you needed.<br>
<br>
This gathered all our components in a single place, let us determine priority and we had few (zero?) problems. If you really needed a spell, she would help you find out where the component dropped so you could go farm it yourself.<br>
<br>
